create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_psa_private_service_accesses
filters compartmentId, displayName, serviceId,
id; Adopt only a unique exact
ListPrivateServiceAccesses match on
compartmentId plus displayName plus serviceId
whose returned subnetId also matches and whose
lifecycle is ACTIVE, CREATING, or UPDATING;
duplicate matches fail, and pre-create lookup is
skipped when compartmentId, subnetId, serviceId,
or displayName is empty.
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
Create, update, and delete persist the in-flight
OCI work request in `status.async.current`,
normalize PSA `OperationStatus*` values into
shared async classes, and normalize work-request
`OperationType*` values into
create/update/delete phases before deriving
conditions and requeue behavior.
Create prefers the returned
`PrivateServiceAccess` body when OCI exposes an
identifier and otherwise recovers the OCID from
work-request resources before polling
`GetPrivateServiceAccess`. Update also gates
completion on a succeeded work request plus a
readable `GetPrivateServiceAccess`.
Only `definedTags`, `freeformTags`,
`securityAttributes`, `displayName`,
`description`, and `nsgIds` reconcile in place.
`compartmentId`, `subnetId`, `serviceId`, and
`ipv4Ip` remain replacement-only drift, so the
published runtime never exercises provider-only
`ChangePrivateServiceAccessCompartment`.
Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats `FAILED` and
`NEEDS_ATTENTION` as terminal failure without
requeue, and delete retains the finalizer until
`GetPrivateServiceAccess` or fallback
`ListPrivateServiceAccesses` confirms the
resource is deleted or not found.
